Pt(s)  ∣ H2(g, 1 bar)  ∣ H+ (aq, 1 M)  ∣ ∣ Cu2+ (aq, 1 M)   ∣ Cu
is 0.34 V and it is also the value for the standard electrode potential of the half-cell corresponding to the reaction:
