Sometimes metals like platinum or gold are used as inert electrodes.", "fibs": ["electrode"]}
{"text": "They do not participate in the reaction but provide their surface for oxidation or reduction reactions and for the conduction of electrons.", "fibs": ["reaction"]}
{"text": "For example, Pt is used in the following half-cells:
Hydrogen electrode: Pt(s) | H2(g) | H+(aq)
With half-cell reaction: H+ (aq)+ e– → ½ H2(g)
Bromine electrode: Pt(s) | Br2(aq) | Br–(aq)
