{"text": "3.6 Batteries
Any battery (actually it may have one or more than one cell connected in series) or cell that we use as a source of electrical energy is basically a galvanic cell where the chemical energy of the redox reaction is converted into electrical energy.", "fibs": ["battery"]}
{"text": "However, for a battery to be of practical use it should be reasonably light, compact and its voltage should not vary appreciably during its use.", "fibs": ["battery"]}
{"text": "3.6.1 Primary Batteries
In the primary batteries, the reaction occurs only once and after use over a period of time battery becomes dead and cannot be reused again.", "fibs": ["reaction"]}
{"text": "The most familiar example of this type is the dry cell (known as Leclanche cell after its discoverer) which is used commonly in our transistors and clocks.", "fibs": ["example"]}
{"text": "The cell consists of a zinc container that also acts as anode and the cathode is a carbon (graphite) rod surrounded by powdered manganese dioxide and carbon (Fig.3.8).", "fibs": ["cell"]}
{"text": "The space between the electrodes is filled by a moist paste of ammonium chloride (NH4Cl) and zinc chloride (ZnCl2).", "fibs": ["space"]}
{"text": "The electrode reactions are complex, but they can be written approximately as follows :
Anode: Zn(s) → Zn2+ + 2e–

Cathode: MnO2+ NH4++ e–→ MnO(OH) + NH3


Fig.", "fibs": ["electrode"]}
{"text": "3.8: A commercial dry cell consists of a graphite (carbon) cathode in a zinc container; the latter acts as the anode.", "fibs": ["cell"]}
{"text": "In the reaction at cathode, manganese is reduced from the + 4 oxidation state to the +3 state.", "fibs": ["reaction"]}
{"text": "Ammonia produced in the reaction forms a complex with Zn2+ to give [Zn (NH3)4]2+.", "fibs": ["Ammonia"]}
{"text": "The cell has a potential of nearly 1.5 V.

Mercury cell, (Fig.", "fibs": ["cell"]}
{"text": "3.9) suitable for low current devices like hearing aids, watches, etc.", "fibs": ["hearing"]}
{"text": "consists of zinc – mercury amalgam as anode and a paste of HgO and carbon as the cathode.", "fibs": ["zinc"]}
{"text": "The electrolyte is a paste of KOH and ZnO.", "fibs": ["electrolyte"]}
{"text": "The electrode reactions for the cell are given below:
